Incremental loading since last January crust so couldn’t clearly tell the exact new snow depth. So measured down to ground. On arrival could observe snow unloading coincident with light wind gusts. Snow did not seem to adhere to the trees very well on this storm. Presumably cold light low density snow with low adhesion. Did only snow depths today and did 3 FSD at the sr50 and T1 pt 1 and pt 10. At each FSD needed three vertical to get fresh snowfall of 30 cm. Only GNSSd the open points to not unload snow out of tree for post snow survey drone flight. Tree snow samples taken directly under flagger
wx: ~ 30 mm over last 48 hr, unloading observed w wind gusts during survey - most of snow still in tree after survey
sample_notes: 14 cm new snow in tree well adjacent to pt 1, took rho in treewell adjacent to pt 1 only surface sample ( 0-10), snow temp -12 C
